# Audit Columns

Every **mutable** business table must include:

- `created_at timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now()`
- `updated_at timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now()`
- `created_by uuid REFERENCES auth.users(id)`
- `updated_by uuid REFERENCES auth.users(id)`

Attach trigger: `BEFORE INSERT OR UPDATE EXECUTE FUNCTION public.set_row_audit()`

## Append-only exceptions

Document in `docs/database/table-dictionary.md`: `financial_events`, `platform_audit_logs`, `enrollment_history`, `auth_audit_logs` — `created_by` only, no `updated_by`.

Run `pnpm audit:schema` before committing migrations.
